

static variable:

class Employee{
  static String company = "infosys";
  int id;
}
Employee e1 = new Employee();
Employee e2 = new Employee();

System.out.println(e1.company); // Infosys
System.out.println(e2.company); // Infosys


only one copy of company exist
Static vairale are shared across all objects!

Static method: Static methods can be called without creating an object.

class Utils {
    static void printMsg() {
        System.out.println("Hello");
    }
}

we can call without object

Utils.printMsg(); is possible

3. STATIC BLOCK
---------------

class Test {
    static {
        System.out.println("Static block executed");
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println("Main method");
    }
}

output:
Static block executed
Main method

used for initilaze static data  &
loading driver
static vlock execute once when the class is loaded

Can we use static with Class?
‚ùå NO
static class Test { } // ‚ùå invalid

but static inner class is allowded

WHY main METHOD IS STATIC (üî• INTERVIEW Q)
public static void main(String[] args)
üìå Best answer:
‚ÄúJVM needs to call main without creating an object, so it must be static

REAL PROJECT CONTEXT (IMPRESSIVE)

Constants ‚Üí static final
Utility methods ‚Üí static
Configuration values ‚Üí static
üìå Smart line:
‚ÄúStatic is commonly used for constants and utility methods.‚Äù

1. static method cannot direclty access instance variables
static blong to class
instance variable belong to objects
At the time a static method runs, no object may exist

class Test {
  int x = 10;
  static void show() {
      System.out.println(x) ;// compile time error
  }
}

correct way:

Static method can access instance data only through an object
class Test {
    int x = 10;

    static void show() {
        Test obj = new Test();
        System.out.println(obj.x); // ‚úÖ allowed
    }
}

